      "identifier": "inconsistent_contract_catalog_pattern",
      "summary": "Contract catalog definitions use inconsistent declaration models across files, creating drift-prone coupling inside the contracts boundary.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/startram_contracts.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "protocol_contracts.go defines IDs/metadata as named constants, then composes entries from those constants.",
        "startram_contracts.go hardcodes ID/version text in the catalog entry and then derives public metadata variables from that mutable entry (`startramApiConnectionErrorContract.Descriptor...`).",
        "Both files maintain separate package-level mutable spec slices (`protocolContractCatalogSpecs`, `startramContractCatalogSpecs`), duplicating registry mechanics instead of enforcing one canonical pattern."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Adopt a single contract declaration architecture for the package (e.g., immutable spec constants + shared builder/registration helper), and migrate both files to it so metadata, IDs, and catalog assembly follow one invariant path.",
